com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.connection

Class NullConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.AbstractConfigurable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.connection.ConnectionBase
        • com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.connection.NullConnection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Connection, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, Serializable

    public class NullConnection
extends ConnectionBase
    Dummy connection useful for tests and benchmarking.

    The NullConnection can save bytes written to its OutputStream to an internal buffer. This buffer can then subsequently be played back into its InputStream. Buffering is off by default. It is turned on/off by called the record(boolean) method.
